WEBVTT

00:01.084 --> 00:03.128
I really want to build a family
with you.

00:03.128 --> 00:05.380
I don't want to have
another kid.

00:05.380 --> 00:08.008
Previously on
"A Million Little Things"...

00:08.008 --> 00:10.677
Tyrell. Why is Child Services
looking for you?

00:10.677 --> 00:11.929
My mom wasn't born here.

00:11.929 --> 00:13.222
ICE. They took her.

00:13.222 --> 00:14.473
We want to foster you.

00:14.473 --> 00:16.683
Only if it's okay with you
and your mom.

00:16.683 --> 00:18.519
I would really like that.

00:18.519 --> 00:19.895
Maggie:
Did he touch you?

00:19.895 --> 00:22.731
No.
He just touched himself.

00:22.731 --> 00:23.899
It's my fault.

00:23.899 --> 00:25.567
I told him
that she lost her father.

00:25.567 --> 00:28.028
I told him how much
she needed this program,

00:28.028 --> 00:30.113
and he never would have known
any of that if it wasn't for me.
No.

00:30.113 --> 00:32.282
Sophie's decided
to go to the police today.

00:32.282 --> 00:34.201
Any possibility
of corroborating evidence

00:34.201 --> 00:35.994
could really help our case
against Peter.

00:35.994 --> 00:38.080
I'm not giving you
my daughter's diary.

00:38.080 --> 00:41.291
This is an agreement for us
to have joint custody of Theo.

00:41.291 --> 00:42.501
Woman: I'm the one
who hit you.

00:42.501 --> 00:44.419
[ Voice breaking ]
I am so sorry.

00:44.419 --> 00:46.255
I want to take Charlie,
Danny, and Sophie

00:46.255 --> 00:47.839
and go back to France.

00:47.839 --> 00:50.842
Your daughter got assaulted
by a monster

00:50.842 --> 00:52.261
who might not have done
what he did

00:52.261 --> 00:54.179
if he knew there was someone
here protecting her!

00:54.179 --> 00:55.764
You weren't able
to stop it.

00:55.764 --> 01:00.102
♪♪

01:01.228 --> 01:04.189
[ Door closes ]

01:04.189 --> 01:06.316
[ Sighs ]

01:06.316 --> 01:12.447
♪♪

01:12.447 --> 01:14.283
Hey, man.

01:14.283 --> 01:17.911
♪♪

01:17.911 --> 01:20.330
I'm sorry.

01:20.330 --> 01:22.291
I just had to
take care of something.

01:22.291 --> 01:24.084
Yeah.

01:24.084 --> 01:26.169
[ Smooches ]

01:26.169 --> 01:27.671
♪♪

01:27.671 --> 01:29.631
[ Groans ]

01:29.631 --> 01:31.091
♪♪

01:31.091 --> 01:34.386
[ Cellphone beeps ]

01:34.386 --> 01:36.221
Darcy: Hey, it's me.

01:36.221 --> 01:39.349
I know we left things
in a weird place earlier,

01:39.349 --> 01:41.518
and I'm sorry.

01:41.518 --> 01:45.480
The thing is,
after I got divorced...

01:45.480 --> 01:48.317
I promised myself that
no matter who I dated,

01:48.317 --> 01:49.901
I wouldn't
have another kid.

01:51.987 --> 01:54.114
But that was before
I fell in love with you.

01:56.992 --> 02:01.038
The fact is, I watched you for
months take care of two kids

02:01.038 --> 02:02.748
you had no relation to,

02:02.748 --> 02:04.249
and there wasn't a minute
you made them feel like

02:04.249 --> 02:06.209
you weren't their family.

02:08.420 --> 02:11.465
Gary, you have
proven to me every day

02:11.465 --> 02:13.759
that you would be
an incredible father.

02:17.262 --> 02:20.682
So, if having kids
is something you want...

02:22.059 --> 02:25.395
...well, then...

02:25.395 --> 02:27.064
I know the perfect
three‐bedroom

02:27.064 --> 02:29.733
we should make an offer on.

02:29.733 --> 02:32.110
Call me.

02:32.110 --> 02:33.278
[ Sighs ]

02:33.278 --> 02:39.701
♪♪

02:39.701 --> 02:46.416
♪♪

02:46.416 --> 02:48.877
[ Washing machine chimes ]

02:48.877 --> 02:51.046
[ Sniffles ]

02:51.046 --> 02:53.048
♪♪

03:00.472 --> 03:01.807
Oh, no, no.
Babe, babe.

03:01.807 --> 03:03.600
I love you and I‐I will do
anything for you,

03:03.600 --> 03:05.686
but I‐I think 3 1/2 pounds
of pancetta is my limit.

03:05.686 --> 03:06.687
Oh, come on.

03:06.687 --> 03:07.896
We got to get rid of
all this food.

03:07.896 --> 03:09.606
Tyrell and I already
dropped two crates

03:09.606 --> 03:10.649
to the women's shelter.

03:10.649 --> 03:11.983
It's all their fridge
could hold.

03:11.983 --> 03:13.318
Half a scoop.

03:14.653 --> 03:16.196
Did I say half a scoop
or half a tub?

03:16.196 --> 03:17.364
That's ‐‐ That's half.

03:17.364 --> 03:18.907
But it's not.

03:18.907 --> 03:20.992
So, Ms. Howard,
it's your first day off

03:20.992 --> 03:22.494
in, what, two years.

03:22.494 --> 03:24.579
Do you have any plans
whatsoever other than

03:24.579 --> 03:26.957
stuffing your husband
with time‐sensitive meat?

03:26.957 --> 03:29.543
Uh, I'm just working on
my message.

03:29.543 --> 03:31.586
What's going on
on your laptop?

03:31.586 --> 03:34.256
Well, I just uploaded
our finished documentary.

03:34.256 --> 03:36.299
I entered my credit card
information,

03:36.299 --> 03:37.467
and once we hit that
"submit" button,

03:37.467 --> 03:39.136
Tyrell and I will
officially be entered

03:39.136 --> 03:40.429
into the
NEFI Film Festival.

03:40.429 --> 03:42.097
[ Door closes ]
Well, what you
waiting for?

03:42.097 --> 03:44.307
I'm waiting on
my producing partner,

03:44.307 --> 03:46.184
who took my headphones
again.

03:46.184 --> 03:48.562
Yeah, love you, too.
Bye.

03:48.562 --> 03:49.563
[ Cellphone beeps ]

03:49.563 --> 03:51.356
How's your mom?

03:51.356 --> 03:53.233
Uh, she's okay.

03:53.233 --> 03:55.986
Uh, apparently she reconnected
with some childhood friends

03:55.986 --> 03:57.737
and they're letting her
stay with them.

03:57.737 --> 03:59.573
And she found some
temporary work, too.

03:59.573 --> 04:01.825
That must make you
feel better.

04:01.825 --> 04:04.703
I mean, she's still sleeping
on someone's couch.

04:04.703 --> 04:06.246
And it's all my fault.

04:06.246 --> 04:10.333
Tyrell, you did not get
your mother deported.

04:10.333 --> 04:13.128
And it sounds like
she's doing okay.

04:13.128 --> 04:15.005
And what she wants is
for you to take advantage

04:15.005 --> 04:17.757
of the opportunities
you have here.

04:17.757 --> 04:20.469
Speaking of which,
if we get into this festival,

04:20.469 --> 04:23.305
we are doing a road trip all
over New England this summer.

04:23.305 --> 04:25.807
All we need is for someone
to hit that submit button,

04:25.807 --> 04:27.142
just someone.

04:27.142 --> 04:29.227
I don't know who
that someone is,

04:29.227 --> 04:30.896
but we need ‐‐
Someone who can spell.

04:30.896 --> 04:32.189
What?

04:32.189 --> 04:34.357
You wrote
"Dome Howard".

04:34.357 --> 04:35.942
You misspelled
your own name, man.

04:35.942 --> 04:37.110
Well,
you take that attitude,

04:37.110 --> 04:38.361
you want to pay
the admission fee, too?

04:38.361 --> 04:39.905
No, that's all you,
Dome.

04:39.905 --> 04:42.991
Just hit the submit button.
Submit!

04:42.991 --> 04:44.951
There you go.
I'll just check everything.

04:44.951 --> 04:46.411
Spielberg.
Boom.

04:46.411 --> 04:48.622
Hey.
Jordan Peele.
I'm with that.

04:48.622 --> 04:50.499
Alright, y'all, quiet down.
I have to record my message.

04:50.499 --> 04:52.000
Hey, quiet on the set,
y'all!

04:52.000 --> 04:53.877
Quiet on the set!

04:53.877 --> 04:55.962
Please? Okay?
We're rolling.

04:55.962 --> 04:57.756
Have some respect
for my actors.

04:57.756 --> 04:59.216
[ Cellphone beeps ]

04:59.216 --> 05:01.343
You've reached
Someday restaurant.

05:01.343 --> 05:04.262
This is Executive Chef
Regina Howard,

05:04.262 --> 05:06.556
and on behalf of
the entire Someday family,

05:06.556 --> 05:08.767
I'd like to thank you
for your patronage and support

05:08.767 --> 05:10.644
these last two years,

05:10.644 --> 05:14.731
especially these last
few months.

05:14.731 --> 05:18.068
As you may have heard...

05:18.068 --> 05:19.528
we've had to shut
our doors,

05:19.528 --> 05:23.615
but our restaurant will be back,
in some way, someday...

05:23.615 --> 05:28.161
♪♪

05:28.161 --> 05:30.872
And when that time comes,
we'll be better than ever.

05:30.872 --> 05:32.916
Until then,
thanks for everything.

05:32.916 --> 05:34.459
[ Cellphone chimes ]

05:34.459 --> 05:36.378
[ Sighs ]

05:36.378 --> 05:41.091
♪♪

05:41.091 --> 05:43.176
Did you just
kiss your own hand?

05:43.176 --> 05:44.970
I meant to kiss yours.
Mm.

05:44.970 --> 05:45.971
That was weird.

05:45.971 --> 05:47.848
[ Laughter ]

05:47.848 --> 05:49.266
Tyrell: Classic Dome.

05:49.266 --> 05:58.441
♪♪

05:58.441 --> 06:00.360
[ Sighs ]

06:00.360 --> 06:05.824
♪♪

06:05.824 --> 06:11.454
♪♪

06:11.454 --> 06:13.540
[ Wheelchair approaches ]

06:13.540 --> 06:14.541
Hey.

06:14.541 --> 06:15.584
You awake?

06:17.711 --> 06:19.546
I am now.

06:19.546 --> 06:22.257
What's going on, man?
Everything alright?

06:22.257 --> 06:23.300
No.

06:27.178 --> 06:28.555
Something happened
last night.

06:31.683 --> 06:35.395
I got a call from
the person who hit me.

06:35.395 --> 06:36.813
What?

06:38.398 --> 06:39.524
W‐What did he say?

06:39.524 --> 06:41.776
She.

06:41.776 --> 06:45.822
I, uh...recorded as much of it
as I could.

06:45.822 --> 06:47.616
Theo left this in my car.

06:49.910 --> 06:52.203
Woman: I'm the one
who hit you.

06:52.203 --> 06:54.623
I wanted to say I'm sorry.

06:54.623 --> 06:55.790
Eddie: How did you
get my number?

06:55.790 --> 06:57.959
I am so sorry.

06:57.959 --> 07:00.086
Okay, okay, I'm coming.

07:00.086 --> 07:01.963
What? No, no.
Who is this?

07:01.963 --> 07:04.633
Hello? Hello?

07:06.551 --> 07:10.096
She called from
a blocked number.

07:10.096 --> 07:12.515
I went online to try and
figure out ways to trace it,

07:12.515 --> 07:14.267
but none of
the suggestions worked.

07:15.810 --> 07:18.772
Wow. Wow.

07:18.772 --> 07:19.814
[ Grunts ]

07:19.814 --> 07:21.399
That's a lot to take in.

07:21.399 --> 07:23.360
Uh...

07:23.360 --> 07:24.486
but if you're looking
for a silver lining,

07:24.486 --> 07:25.862
after hearing
that recording,

07:25.862 --> 07:28.406
I'm 99% sure Katherine
wasn't the one who hit you.

07:28.406 --> 07:29.616
[ Chuckles ]

07:29.616 --> 07:32.494
Why would she call if
she was just gonna hang up?

07:32.494 --> 07:34.496
Hasn't she done
enough to me already?

07:34.496 --> 07:37.415
Look, you ‐‐
you just found out

07:37.415 --> 07:40.168
Delilah's gonna take
Charlie back to France.

07:40.168 --> 07:42.337
You're in the middle
of a divorce, right?

07:42.337 --> 07:45.965
And I might have to join
a 12‐step program

07:45.965 --> 07:48.218
just to deal with hearing
about the stuff that
you're going through.

07:48.218 --> 07:49.886
I‐I don't want this
to cause you to nosedive.

07:49.886 --> 07:51.346
I‐I get it.

07:51.346 --> 07:53.390
It's just...

07:53.390 --> 07:56.851
this woman put me
in a wheelchair,

07:56.851 --> 07:59.938
and after months of
wondering who it was,

07:59.938 --> 08:01.481
of trying to
move past it,

08:01.481 --> 08:04.526
she wants to call me
to say she's sorry?

08:04.526 --> 08:06.111
Why?

08:06.111 --> 08:08.488
So she can live her life
like nothing happened?

08:08.488 --> 08:10.490
I hear you, Ed.

08:10.490 --> 08:11.908
You want justice.

08:11.908 --> 08:15.412
Believe me...

08:15.412 --> 08:17.747
nobody understands that
more than me.

08:17.747 --> 08:20.750
♪♪

08:20.750 --> 08:24.170
I just don't want you to do
something you'll regret, okay?

08:26.214 --> 08:27.882
No, you're right.

08:27.882 --> 08:36.808
♪♪

08:36.808 --> 08:40.270
I can't believe she didn't
come home last night.

08:40.270 --> 08:42.313
Well, she can't
be angry forever.

08:43.940 --> 08:46.609
You're right.
She can.

08:46.609 --> 08:48.820
I think we both know
where she gets that.

08:50.363 --> 08:52.907
Dad.
I was talking about Dad.

08:52.907 --> 08:53.908
Oh.
[ Laughs ]

08:53.908 --> 08:56.953
[ Cellphone vibrating ]

08:56.953 --> 08:58.621
Hello?

08:58.621 --> 08:59.664
This is she.

09:02.333 --> 09:03.877
Oh, my God.

09:03.877 --> 09:08.131
♪♪

09:08.131 --> 09:11.718
[ Sighs, groans ]

09:11.718 --> 09:13.762
Good morning.

09:13.762 --> 09:15.930
Sorry about the couch.
It was my grandma's.

09:15.930 --> 09:18.516
Which, in hindsight,
explains the hump.

09:18.516 --> 09:20.101
[ Chuckles ]

09:20.101 --> 09:23.271
Well, actually, last night was
the best I've slept in months.

09:23.271 --> 09:25.315
I thought after I
posted the podcast,

09:25.315 --> 09:26.816
I'd be too anxious
to sleep.

09:26.816 --> 09:28.234
How are you feeling?

09:29.944 --> 09:33.740
I'm a little scared how people
are gonna react, but...

09:33.740 --> 09:35.825
so glad I did it.

09:35.825 --> 09:37.202
[ Cellphone vibrating ]

09:37.202 --> 09:39.204
Ah, that's probably
your mom checking in.

09:39.204 --> 09:41.539
I texted her to let her know
you were sleeping over.

09:41.539 --> 09:43.958
Oh, well, unless
she's calling to apologize,

09:43.958 --> 09:45.710
she can talk to
my voicemail.

09:45.710 --> 09:48.004
You know, phone it in,
like she has this entire year.

09:48.004 --> 09:49.839
Oh, it's not her.

09:49.839 --> 09:51.382
I actually don't know
who this is.

09:51.382 --> 09:52.967
Oh, so you're gonna answer
a call you don't know,

09:52.967 --> 09:54.344
but not your mother?

09:54.344 --> 09:55.637
That's right.

09:55.637 --> 09:56.554
Hello?

09:56.554 --> 09:58.139
Hey, Sophie.

09:58.139 --> 10:00.934
It's, uh, Detective Saunders
with the Brookline PD.

10:00.934 --> 10:03.269
Oh.

10:03.269 --> 10:04.646
Hi.

10:04.646 --> 10:08.691
I just wanted to follow up
with you about yesterday.

10:08.691 --> 10:10.276
I know your mom told you
that we don't have

10:10.276 --> 10:12.195
enough evidence
to file charges,

10:12.195 --> 10:15.532
and it must've been really
upsetting for you to hear.

10:15.532 --> 10:17.367
Yeah.

10:17.367 --> 10:19.035
I mean, I‐I get it,

10:19.035 --> 10:21.704
but...
it's still not fair.

10:21.704 --> 10:24.415
I understand that.
Believe me. I do.

10:24.415 --> 10:26.417
I am sorry.

10:26.417 --> 10:28.378
You must be feeling
a lot of anger.

10:28.378 --> 10:30.505
Yeah, but I'm
dealing with it.

10:30.505 --> 10:32.590
Actually, I‐I spent
the night at my friend
Maggie's last night.

10:32.590 --> 10:34.801
She let me tell my story
on her podcast.

10:34.801 --> 10:36.761
You were at your friend's
last night?

10:36.761 --> 10:38.471
Yeah, I'm actually still here.
Why?

10:38.471 --> 10:40.515
Well, the other reason
I'm calling

10:40.515 --> 10:42.183
is because I wanted you
to hear this from me.

10:42.183 --> 10:45.395
Peter Benoit
was attacked last night.

10:45.395 --> 10:46.646
What?

10:46.646 --> 10:49.941
♪♪

10:49.941 --> 10:51.985
[ Over speakerphone ]
Peter's wife called 911.

10:51.985 --> 10:54.362
It appears to be
a home invasion.

10:54.362 --> 10:56.865
A guitar and some of Peter's
other stuff is missing.

10:56.865 --> 10:59.075
Right now, we're investigating
it as a burglary.

11:00.910 --> 11:04.038
Uh...did he get hurt?

11:04.038 --> 11:06.916
He was beaten
pretty badly, yeah.

11:06.916 --> 11:08.459
We're not sure yet
if he's gonna make it.

11:08.459 --> 11:13.089
♪♪

11:17.552 --> 11:19.137
♪♪

11:19.137 --> 11:22.348
Hey, Steel Wheels.

11:22.348 --> 11:24.017
You left clothes
in the dryer again.

11:25.894 --> 11:27.187
Are these yours?

11:27.187 --> 11:29.022
Those are Theo's.

11:29.022 --> 11:31.357
You're probably more of
a Spider‐Man guy?

11:31.357 --> 11:32.984
[ Knock on door ]

11:32.984 --> 11:34.944
Hello?

11:34.944 --> 11:37.071
[ Door closes ]
Hey.

11:37.071 --> 11:40.200
Hey.

11:40.200 --> 11:42.452
Oop.
She's got the duffel bag.

11:42.452 --> 11:43.870
That means she's here
to see you, pal.

11:43.870 --> 11:45.163
But if you don't mind,

11:45.163 --> 11:47.707
I'd appreciate it
if I could say hello first.

11:47.707 --> 11:49.500
Eddie:
Seems reasonable.
Thank you.

11:49.500 --> 11:52.337
While I have
you both here ‐‐

11:52.337 --> 11:55.298
I am looking at
an apartment today.

11:55.298 --> 11:57.050
What?
Katherine and I talked.

11:57.050 --> 11:58.301
We came up with
a custody plan

11:58.301 --> 12:01.179
for me to look after
Theo on my own.

12:01.179 --> 12:04.682
Gary is officially off the hook.
Yeah.

12:04.682 --> 12:07.602
And I'd love to chat about it,
but if I stay here any longer,

12:07.602 --> 12:09.646
I might not make it to
the bathroom in time

12:09.646 --> 12:13.149
to complete Step One
of that plan.

12:13.149 --> 12:15.151
I'll be back in a jiff.

12:15.151 --> 12:17.028
And, uh,
while I'm in there,

12:17.028 --> 12:20.907
I will change into
my robot underpants.

12:20.907 --> 12:22.325
His what?

12:22.325 --> 12:23.660
Don't worry about it.
It's between men.

12:23.660 --> 12:25.203
[ Door closes ]
Hmm.

12:30.083 --> 12:33.211
So, I didn't
hear from you.

12:33.211 --> 12:35.797
Even though I left you
the nicest message

12:35.797 --> 12:37.173
I've ever left anyone.

12:37.173 --> 12:39.676
You left me a‐a message
last night?

12:39.676 --> 12:42.470
It must be on somebody else's
voicemail.

12:42.470 --> 12:44.472
I‐I don't mean to alarm you,
but you may have

12:44.472 --> 12:46.599
agreed to have
someone else's baby.

12:46.599 --> 12:47.892
[ Chuckles ]

12:47.892 --> 12:50.186
Hey. I'm so sorry
I didn't answer.

12:50.186 --> 12:51.437
Last night
was just crazy.

12:51.437 --> 12:53.273
Where were you?

12:53.273 --> 12:55.900
My dad's.
Yeah.

12:55.900 --> 12:58.152
Telling him that you and me
and Liam and Colin

12:58.152 --> 13:01.781
are all moving
to Lenox.

13:01.781 --> 13:04.367
So I was there for a while,
'cause I also had to explain

13:04.367 --> 13:05.868
that you agreed to have
some other dude's baby.

13:05.868 --> 13:08.496
Oh, you're an ass.
[ Laughs ]

13:08.496 --> 13:11.582
Listen, lady, I will put one
in you right now.

13:11.582 --> 13:13.001
Mm.

13:13.001 --> 13:16.629
Okay. I'll call the other guy
and tell him that it's off.

13:16.629 --> 13:18.423
[ Sighs ]

13:18.423 --> 13:20.550
♪♪

13:22.927 --> 13:26.222
[ Radio static, tuning ]

13:26.222 --> 13:28.516
Dr. Stacy:
Well, that's your problem!

13:28.516 --> 13:31.060
How can you expect your
boyfriend to respect you

13:31.060 --> 13:33.521
if you don't
respect yourself?

13:33.521 --> 13:36.774
Woman caller:
So, you're saying I should pay
half the utilities?

13:36.774 --> 13:39.193
I'm saying if he
really loved you,

13:39.193 --> 13:40.737
he'd make an honest woman
of you,

13:40.737 --> 13:42.321
and you'd be paying
those utilities

13:42.321 --> 13:43.948
from a joint
checking account.

13:43.948 --> 13:45.450
I'm Dr. Stacy.

13:45.450 --> 13:47.160
Not saying what
you want to hear...

13:47.160 --> 13:49.162
Saying what
you need to hear.
...saying what
you need to hear.

13:49.162 --> 13:51.289
And we'll be
right back.

13:51.289 --> 13:53.583
Claudia,
are you kidding me?

13:53.583 --> 13:56.377
I have to spend my break doing
a stupid meet and greet?

13:56.377 --> 13:58.755
I swear to God, if you had
any less brain cells,

13:58.755 --> 14:02.550
I could write off hiring you
as a charitable donation.

14:02.550 --> 14:03.634
Why ‐‐ Why are we doing

14:03.634 --> 14:05.344
back‐to‐back
relationship calls?

14:05.344 --> 14:07.847
If I wanted to hear
a bunch of whiny bitches

14:07.847 --> 14:10.058
drone on about their
horrible marriages,

14:10.058 --> 14:11.768
I'd go visit
my sisters.
[ Gasps ]

14:11.768 --> 14:14.062
Claudia:
Dr. Stacy, the mic!

14:17.231 --> 14:18.941
Announcer: You're listening to
"The Dr. Stacy Show" ‐‐

14:18.941 --> 14:22.361
Real talk. Real help.

14:22.361 --> 14:24.530
Real screwed.

14:24.530 --> 14:25.615
Oh.

14:25.615 --> 14:32.622
♪♪

14:32.622 --> 14:39.629
♪♪

14:39.629 --> 14:41.756
Good.
You're back.

14:41.756 --> 14:42.840
We need to
talk about Mom.

14:42.840 --> 14:44.008
[ Scoffs ]
Well, let me guess ‐‐

14:44.008 --> 14:44.967
she convinced you to be okay
with everything,

14:44.967 --> 14:46.719
and now you're
on her side.

14:46.719 --> 14:48.304
It's a little more
complicated than that.

14:48.304 --> 14:49.847
Really? How?

14:49.847 --> 14:51.724
I mean, she abandons us
for months,

14:51.724 --> 14:53.351
decides to come back
for two days,

14:53.351 --> 14:54.894
just so she can uproot
our entire lives ‐‐

14:54.894 --> 14:55.978
Grandpa had a stroke.

14:58.523 --> 15:00.316
What?

15:00.316 --> 15:01.692
Where is she?

15:01.692 --> 15:03.736
In the kitchen,
trying to book a flight.

15:03.736 --> 15:04.862
Delilah: There's no flights
till tomorrow morning?

15:04.862 --> 15:06.364
I need to get home.

15:06.364 --> 15:08.282
I don't know if my dad's gonna
make it through the night.

15:10.910 --> 15:13.788
Okay. Right.

15:13.788 --> 15:15.706
Alright, you know what?
Yeah.

15:15.706 --> 15:17.083
I can't believe this.

15:17.083 --> 15:18.918
I know.
Keep me posted.

15:18.918 --> 15:23.256
It's really sad,
but he had a really full life.

15:23.256 --> 15:25.466
I‐I mean, I'm sad
about Grandpa,

15:25.466 --> 15:28.094
but I'm just going through
a lot right now,

15:28.094 --> 15:30.138
and once again, that's just
gonna take a back seat to her.

15:30.138 --> 15:31.305
I mean, God, watch.

15:31.305 --> 15:32.765
I'm gonna have to
help her through this,

15:32.765 --> 15:36.352
even though she was barely there
for me when I needed her.

15:36.352 --> 15:37.436
Soph...

15:40.398 --> 15:44.485
...how angry are you at Dad
for leaving us?

15:44.485 --> 15:45.611
What?

15:45.611 --> 15:47.196
I‐I'm not.

15:47.196 --> 15:49.991
I‐I mean, I'm sad and I'm hurt,
but I'm not mad.

15:51.826 --> 15:54.078
Dad was suffering.

15:54.078 --> 15:55.746
Yeah.

15:55.746 --> 15:58.916
So is Mom.

15:58.916 --> 16:01.544
And you won't have to
help her through it.

16:01.544 --> 16:03.880
I'm going to.

16:03.880 --> 16:06.048
I'm gonna go with her.

16:06.048 --> 16:08.176
To ‐‐ To France?
For how long?

16:09.802 --> 16:12.346
For as long
as she needs me.

16:12.346 --> 16:21.314
♪♪

16:25.776 --> 16:28.196
How many more?
[ Exhales deeply ]

16:28.196 --> 16:29.447
Next session, I'm
gonna introduce you
to the new therapist

16:29.447 --> 16:31.657
who's gonna be taking over
all of my clients.

16:31.657 --> 16:33.659
You guys have
so much in common.
[ Grunts ]

16:33.659 --> 16:36.495
He's crazy about hockey, and
he eats with his mouth open.

16:36.495 --> 16:37.496
[ Door closes ]
[ Grunts ]

16:37.496 --> 16:38.956
What?
My new trainer's Gary?

16:38.956 --> 16:41.083
[ Chuckles ]
How does that work?

16:41.083 --> 16:44.378
Doesn't he and his mouth full
of fries have to go with you?

16:44.378 --> 16:47.048
I'd just like to point out
that these are your fries

16:47.048 --> 16:50.176
that you asked me to get you,
which I did.

16:50.176 --> 16:53.763
And now, I will eat a handful
and chew with my mouth open.

16:53.763 --> 16:55.056
[ Crunching ]

16:55.056 --> 16:57.350
Mmm. Good.

16:57.350 --> 16:58.809
You're gonna miss this.

16:58.809 --> 17:01.562
On the plus side, I'm getting
paid to have this conversation.

17:01.562 --> 17:03.356
[ Cellphone ringing ]
[ Both laugh ]

17:03.356 --> 17:05.441
Oop.

17:05.441 --> 17:07.818
Gotta take a phone call.
Excuse me.

17:07.818 --> 17:09.278
Hello?
Maggie:
Where have you been?

17:09.278 --> 17:10.071
I've been trying
to call you.

17:10.071 --> 17:12.865
Guess who just imploded?

17:12.865 --> 17:14.367
[ Chuckles ]
Actually, I'm gonna tell you.

17:14.367 --> 17:16.035
It was Dr. Stacy.

17:16.035 --> 17:18.412
She had a crazy rant
on the radio this morning,

17:18.412 --> 17:20.164
not realizing that
her mic was still on.

17:20.164 --> 17:22.124
She reamed
her assistant out

17:22.124 --> 17:24.335
while totally
insulting her fans,

17:24.335 --> 17:26.379
and now it has gone viral,

17:26.379 --> 17:28.547
confirming that
there is, in fact, a God.

17:28.547 --> 17:30.758
Oh, if you want,
I will act it out for you,

17:30.758 --> 17:32.843
so please want that.

17:32.843 --> 17:33.886
I'm sorry,
who is this?

17:33.886 --> 17:35.388
Ha ha.

17:35.388 --> 17:37.390
Yeah, I'm gonna send you
the clip right now.

17:37.390 --> 17:39.767
Please commit this to memory,
because later,

17:39.767 --> 17:43.187
I will be playing the
Dr. Stacy to your Claudia.

17:43.187 --> 17:46.190
You have one line,
but it is critical.

17:46.190 --> 17:48.985
"Dr. Stacy, the mic."

17:48.985 --> 17:50.778
Well, it sounds like she got
what was coming to her.

17:50.778 --> 17:52.947
Oh, speaking of which,

17:52.947 --> 17:56.617
you heard about
what happened to Peter?

17:56.617 --> 17:57.785
No.

17:57.785 --> 17:59.412
What ‐‐
What happened to Peter?

17:59.412 --> 18:01.706
Oh, God. Um...

18:01.706 --> 18:04.750
somebody broke into his house
last night and attacked him.

18:06.168 --> 18:08.170
Wow.

18:08.170 --> 18:10.715
Why are all
the good ideas taken?

18:10.715 --> 18:11.966
No, listen.

18:11.966 --> 18:14.218
I‐It was some sort of
robbery or something.

18:14.218 --> 18:16.429
He ‐‐ He's in a coma.

18:16.429 --> 18:20.016
Uh...h‐how's Sophie
taking all this?

18:20.016 --> 18:21.767
She's okay.

18:21.767 --> 18:23.352
I mean, she took it
better than I thought.

18:23.352 --> 18:26.147
And how did you find out?
'Cause, uh...

18:26.147 --> 18:28.566
I'm not seeing anything
about it online.

18:28.566 --> 18:30.568
No, I don't think there would
be anything online yet.

18:30.568 --> 18:32.820
The detective from
the Brookline Police Department

18:32.820 --> 18:35.031
called Sophie this morning.

18:35.031 --> 18:36.032
Wait.

18:36.032 --> 18:37.491
[ Laptop closes ]

18:37.491 --> 18:39.160
Why would
he call Sophie?

18:39.160 --> 18:42.121
I think so that she would
hear it from him?

18:42.121 --> 18:43.956
Once the news
does break,

18:43.956 --> 18:46.125
Peter's name and face
are gonna be everywhere.

18:46.125 --> 18:50.254
That could be really triggering
for her.

18:50.254 --> 18:51.339
Yeah.

18:51.339 --> 18:54.300
[ Knock on door ]

18:54.300 --> 18:56.010
Bloom, I gotta
call you back.

18:56.010 --> 18:57.970
Eddie: No, Gary!
Don't get up!

18:57.970 --> 19:01.057
Let the guy who can't walk
answer it. [ Chuckles ]

19:01.057 --> 19:03.601
I refuse to treat you
any differently!

19:03.601 --> 19:08.147
♪♪

19:08.147 --> 19:10.566
Hi.
I'm looking
for Gary Mendez.

19:10.566 --> 19:13.319
♪♪

19:13.319 --> 19:15.029
Can I help you?

19:15.029 --> 19:16.947
Yeah,
I'm Martin Tisdale.

19:16.947 --> 19:19.367
Okay?

19:19.367 --> 19:21.494
The photographer.

19:21.494 --> 19:22.953
Photographer?

19:25.539 --> 19:27.958
Aren't you putting
your condo on the market?

19:27.958 --> 19:29.585
I'm here to take photos.

19:29.585 --> 19:32.338
Yes.
Uh, I'm sorry.

19:32.338 --> 19:34.799
Get in here, man.
Let's take some photos.

19:34.799 --> 19:36.842
Look,
you dressed up nice.

19:36.842 --> 19:39.136
Make sure we take some
of you, too.

19:40.429 --> 19:42.181
Okay, hand me
another one.

19:42.181 --> 19:43.808
Oh, my God.

19:43.808 --> 19:46.477
This is the first $5
I made at Someday.

19:46.477 --> 19:49.897
I remember because
I wrote my name on the ‐‐

19:49.897 --> 19:51.565
Wait, where's
my signature?

19:53.984 --> 19:56.195
Oh, my God.
[ Gasps ]

19:56.195 --> 19:58.280
This is the $5
I pinned to the wall

19:58.280 --> 19:59.907
to remember to pay that
Girl Scout for those cookies.

19:59.907 --> 20:01.409
I never paid her.

20:01.409 --> 20:03.703
But I insisted
that I did pay her.

20:03.703 --> 20:06.747
Oh, my God.
I gaslit a child.

20:06.747 --> 20:08.541
On the bright side,
free Thin Mints.

20:08.541 --> 20:09.959
[ Chuckles ]

20:11.377 --> 20:12.420
Oh.

20:15.423 --> 20:17.383
What's that?

20:17.383 --> 20:22.555
Um, before the pandemic,
I, uh, created a recipe

20:22.555 --> 20:25.141
f‐for apple soufflé,
and I was planning on

20:25.141 --> 20:27.977
introducing it to the menu,
but...

20:27.977 --> 20:29.937
Nope.
Not going there.

20:29.937 --> 20:32.857
Put it on the shelf, pack it
away with my other emotions.

20:32.857 --> 20:34.483
Attagirl.

20:34.483 --> 20:36.110
[ Cellphone chimes ]

20:36.110 --> 20:41.741
♪♪

20:41.741 --> 20:43.534
What's that?

20:43.534 --> 20:45.202
Nothing.
Uh‐huh.

20:45.202 --> 20:46.287
The way you're
saying "nothing"

20:46.287 --> 20:47.329
makes it sound like
it's something.

20:47.329 --> 20:48.497
What ‐‐
What's going on?

20:48.497 --> 20:52.126
♪♪

20:52.126 --> 20:54.712
A while ago,

20:54.712 --> 20:58.048
I set an alert to let me know
when Haiti's airport reopened.

21:00.468 --> 21:01.969
That's what
that ding was.

21:04.221 --> 21:06.307
We have to
tell Tyrell.

21:06.307 --> 21:07.558
We can't.

21:07.558 --> 21:09.268
Why not?

21:09.268 --> 21:13.522
Because if we tell him...
he'll go.

21:13.522 --> 21:17.526
♪♪

21:24.325 --> 21:27.286
Eddie, you really don't need
to show me your apartment.

21:27.286 --> 21:29.371
Well, it's not just
my apartment.

21:29.371 --> 21:32.750
Theo's gonna be spending
half his time here.

21:32.750 --> 21:35.878
I want to make sure it's a place
you're comfortable with, too.

21:35.878 --> 21:39.048
You really didn't
need to do that.

21:39.048 --> 21:41.258
But I'm ‐‐
I'm glad you did.

21:41.258 --> 21:42.259
[ Door opens ]

21:42.259 --> 21:46.639
[ Sighs ]
Sorry. So sorry.

21:46.639 --> 21:49.767
[ Chuckling ] I had so much
trouble getting over here.

21:49.767 --> 21:53.020
Yeah, sometimes getting
to a place is hard.

21:53.020 --> 21:55.064
Just messing with you.

21:55.064 --> 21:58.317
[ Sighs, chuckles ]
Yeah.

22:01.737 --> 22:03.531
Thank you.

22:03.531 --> 22:05.324
[ Upbeat remix plays ]

22:05.324 --> 22:07.910
♪ Whiny bitches, whiny bitches,
whiny, whiny bitches ♪

22:07.910 --> 22:09.829
[ Laughs ]
♪ Are you kidding me? ♪

22:09.829 --> 22:12.540
♪ I swear to God, I swear to ‐‐
swear to God ♪

22:12.540 --> 22:14.124
♪ Dr. Stacy, the mic ♪

22:14.124 --> 22:16.335
Oh, no.

22:16.335 --> 22:17.962
[ Chuckles ]

22:17.962 --> 22:20.714
[ Ringing ]

22:20.714 --> 22:23.175
Claudia: This is Claudia.
Hey, there.

22:23.175 --> 22:26.470
I just ‐‐ I wanted to check
and see how you're doing.

22:26.470 --> 22:29.932
Maggie, hey.
I guess you heard.

22:29.932 --> 22:31.725
Yeah, I heard

22:31.725 --> 22:34.937
and then re‐heard
and then I re‐re‐heard.

22:34.937 --> 22:37.773
[ Chuckles ]
You're a viral meme.

22:37.773 --> 22:40.276
I'm glad someone
finds it funny.

22:40.276 --> 22:41.902
But, I guess,
the important thing is

22:41.902 --> 22:45.322
now everybody knows how
Dr. Stacy's been treating you.

22:45.322 --> 22:47.283
Yeah, which is great,

22:47.283 --> 22:49.493
except I got fired.

22:49.493 --> 22:51.912
Wait, fired?

22:51.912 --> 22:53.289
Can they do that?

22:53.289 --> 22:56.166
Well...

22:56.166 --> 22:59.211
I mean, I was
Dr. Stacy's assistant.

22:59.211 --> 23:02.131
When they fired her,
there was no need for me.

23:02.131 --> 23:03.716
[ Clicks key ]

23:03.716 --> 23:06.051
♪ Dr. Stacy, the mic ♪

23:06.051 --> 23:08.429
♪ Whiny bitches, whiny bitches,
whiny, whiny bitches ♪
I'm so sorry, Claudia.

23:08.429 --> 23:09.930
♪ Are you kidding me? ♪
Aah.

23:11.015 --> 23:12.349
[ Laptop closes ]

23:12.349 --> 23:15.311
Brandon: The whole place
is wheelchair‐accessible,

23:15.311 --> 23:18.689
as are all
the building's common spaces.

23:18.689 --> 23:21.483
Um, there's designated parking
right near the elevator,

23:21.483 --> 23:26.280
and this apartment
has in‐unit laundry.

23:26.280 --> 23:27.990
What do you think?

23:27.990 --> 23:29.575
I love it.

23:29.575 --> 23:30.868
But I don't want to
love it too much,

23:30.868 --> 23:32.661
in case you haven't
negotiated the rent.

23:32.661 --> 23:33.787
I did.

23:33.787 --> 23:35.456
Then I love it.

23:35.456 --> 23:36.999
Now, is it just
the two of you?

23:36.999 --> 23:38.959
I‐I thought you said
on the phone that you had a kid.

23:38.959 --> 23:40.002
We do, but ‐‐

23:40.002 --> 23:41.003
I'm not moving in.

23:41.003 --> 23:43.255
It's just me
and the kid.

23:43.255 --> 23:44.840
Oh.

23:44.840 --> 23:45.966
I‐I didn't realize.

23:45.966 --> 23:47.676
You two seem to
get along really well.

23:49.762 --> 23:53.223
Wow, I am saying all
the wrong things today.

23:53.223 --> 23:54.683
[ All chuckle ]

23:54.683 --> 23:56.143
Yeah.

23:58.228 --> 23:59.063
Sophie: Hey, Mom.

24:01.482 --> 24:02.483
Hey.

24:04.860 --> 24:07.696
I'm really sorry
about Grandpa.

24:07.696 --> 24:10.032
I know, sweetie.

24:10.032 --> 24:11.367
Listen, I didn't
mean for you

24:11.367 --> 24:13.285
to find out about France
the way you did.

24:13.285 --> 24:14.745
It's just ‐‐

24:14.745 --> 24:16.997
there's just so much going on,
and now with Grandpa ‐‐

24:16.997 --> 24:19.083
You do not
need to explain.

24:22.002 --> 24:23.963
I know how hard it is
to lose your dad.

24:30.427 --> 24:32.304
I'm glad you got to
spend some time with him

24:32.304 --> 24:33.722
when you
came to France.

24:33.722 --> 24:36.058
Me, too.

24:36.058 --> 24:37.768
Uh, if it's
okay with you,

24:37.768 --> 24:39.853
I'd like to
remember him that way.

24:41.355 --> 24:44.191
You're not coming?

24:44.191 --> 24:45.859
No.

24:45.859 --> 24:48.112
Okay. I understand.

24:48.112 --> 24:49.989
I'll be back
as soon as I can,

24:49.989 --> 24:52.741
and then we can figure
everything out, okay?

24:52.741 --> 24:54.868
Well, actually, that's what I
wanted to talk to you about.

24:56.787 --> 24:58.789
I mean, of course, I think
you should come back

24:58.789 --> 25:03.585
as soon as you can, but
I don't think it's right now.

25:03.585 --> 25:06.630
You need to be
in France,

25:06.630 --> 25:09.967
doing all the things
that you need to do.

25:09.967 --> 25:11.176
Just like
I need to be here,

25:11.176 --> 25:12.761
doing all the things
that I need to do.

25:12.761 --> 25:18.517
And asking you to stay is just
as unfair as asking me to go.

25:18.517 --> 25:20.227
[ Sniffles ]

25:20.227 --> 25:22.938
Oh, God.

25:22.938 --> 25:26.150
When did you
get to be so mature?

25:26.150 --> 25:28.777
Well, probably during the four
months that you were in France.

25:28.777 --> 25:31.572
[ Both chuckle ]

25:31.572 --> 25:32.823
[ Sniffles ]

25:32.823 --> 25:34.908
Actually, can you come
downstairs for a sec?

25:34.908 --> 25:37.036
I have
a goodbye present.

25:37.036 --> 25:38.954
♪♪

25:38.954 --> 25:41.165
[ Indistinct conversations ]

25:41.165 --> 25:44.293
Oh, my God.
You guys, what is this?

25:44.293 --> 25:47.046
Rome: Oh, well, we ‐‐
we couldn't let you move

25:47.046 --> 25:48.547
without having
one last pizza night.

25:48.547 --> 25:51.467
It turns out,
I'm still a chef, so...

25:51.467 --> 25:55.095
And for dessert, we will be
having apple soufflé.

25:55.095 --> 25:57.806
Andiamo!

25:57.806 --> 26:00.768
All: Andiamo!

26:00.768 --> 26:03.687
♪♪

26:08.192 --> 26:10.778
[ All shouting "speech" ]

26:10.778 --> 26:13.197
No. No, no.
I'm terrible at speeches.

26:13.197 --> 26:14.573
Gary: Oh, let me guess,
you're gonna use

26:14.573 --> 26:16.992
the "English is my second
language" excuse again?

26:16.992 --> 26:18.243
No, I'm just gonna say

26:18.243 --> 26:20.329
some really bad words
to you in French.

26:20.329 --> 26:21.622
Ooh.

26:21.622 --> 26:24.374
[ Laughter ]

26:24.374 --> 26:26.627
Um, okay.

26:29.546 --> 26:32.382
Um...

26:32.382 --> 26:36.678
Jon always wanted us
to do pizza night

26:36.678 --> 26:40.474
so that no matter what was
going on in our lives,

26:40.474 --> 26:44.853
we could all come together every
Friday and fill up on bread.

26:44.853 --> 26:46.105
[ Laughter ]

26:49.566 --> 26:52.444
I remember one time my dad
came over for pizza night,

26:52.444 --> 26:55.114
and he couldn't remember
Jon was gone.

26:56.949 --> 26:58.951
Um...

26:58.951 --> 27:00.744
the problem is, I can't
look around this house

27:00.744 --> 27:03.330
without remembering
that he is.

27:03.330 --> 27:06.917
There's just
so many memories here ‐‐

27:06.917 --> 27:10.295
so many wonderful memories
that I've made in this house,

27:10.295 --> 27:13.048
a lot of them
with all of you.

27:13.048 --> 27:15.300
[ Voice breaking ]
But, uh, I know that

27:15.300 --> 27:19.555
it's also really important
for me...to make new ones.

27:19.555 --> 27:21.974
[ Sniffles ]

27:21.974 --> 27:25.477
And believe me, the hardest part
of me moving to France

27:25.477 --> 27:27.729
is knowing that I won't be
surrounded by all of you.

27:27.729 --> 27:32.150
Because I love you guys.
[ Sniffles ]

27:32.150 --> 27:33.610
And, uh,
you've gotten me through

27:33.610 --> 27:35.571
the toughest times of my life.

27:37.447 --> 27:39.783
So I just wanted to
say thank you.

27:41.493 --> 27:43.453
Love you.
We love you, D.

27:43.453 --> 27:45.247
‐Love you.
‐We'll miss you, D.

27:45.247 --> 27:47.916
♪♪

27:47.916 --> 27:49.251
Why haven't we
slept together yet?

27:49.251 --> 27:51.169
[ Laughter ]
What? What?

27:51.169 --> 27:53.463
Rome: Hey, what is this?
What is this?

27:53.463 --> 27:55.299
Oh, that was
my outside voice.
What is this?

27:55.299 --> 27:58.844
[ Indistinct conversations ]

27:58.844 --> 28:03.932
♪♪

28:03.932 --> 28:07.561
Babe...shouldn't we
let Tyrell know

28:07.561 --> 28:09.521
that the airport in Haiti
is open?

28:09.521 --> 28:11.732
I mean, he's gonna
find out anyway.

28:11.732 --> 28:14.109
You said it yourself when
he first wanted to go ‐‐

28:14.109 --> 28:17.195
it's dangerous,
and his mom's not set up there.
She is, Rome.

28:17.195 --> 28:19.114
She is now.

28:21.533 --> 28:23.285
I mean, are we not telling him
because it's dangerous

28:23.285 --> 28:25.871
or because we
don't want to lose him?

28:25.871 --> 28:31.043
♪♪

28:31.043 --> 28:32.377
80/20.

28:32.377 --> 28:34.379
Yeah.

28:34.379 --> 28:35.839
But which one's the 80?

28:35.839 --> 28:41.845
♪♪

28:43.013 --> 28:46.141
Well, [sighs]
look at this.

28:46.141 --> 28:48.185
Right back in
our boxing ring.

28:48.185 --> 28:50.103
[ Chuckles ]
You ready for round two?

28:52.439 --> 28:54.983
I checked with the ref.

28:54.983 --> 28:58.111
Turns out, uh...

28:58.111 --> 29:00.322
I shouldn't have
said those things.

29:00.322 --> 29:01.990
But you were
thinking them.

29:01.990 --> 29:04.993
Yeah, but I shouldn't
have said them.

29:04.993 --> 29:06.870
So is this your version
of an apology?

29:06.870 --> 29:08.455
It is.
How am I doing?

29:08.455 --> 29:10.707
Fantastic.

29:10.707 --> 29:13.126
I'm sorry, too,

29:13.126 --> 29:17.589
for everything I said and for
everything that I was thinking.

29:17.589 --> 29:19.758
I know you'd do anything
for this family.

29:21.677 --> 29:24.012
Anything.

29:24.012 --> 29:25.180
Except for a ride
to the airport.

29:25.180 --> 29:26.932
Please ask Rome
for that.

29:26.932 --> 29:29.601
Actually, Eddie's driving me.
He can do that now.

29:29.601 --> 29:31.186
With his
push‐button car?

29:31.186 --> 29:34.106
Great, now I get to
make a hospital run, too.

29:36.858 --> 29:38.986
I'm gonna miss you, D.

29:38.986 --> 29:41.238
I'm gonna miss you, too.

29:41.238 --> 29:44.866
[ Michael Penn's
"No Myth" plays ]

29:44.866 --> 29:46.618
Did you just grab
my ass?

29:46.618 --> 29:48.620
Stop it.
[ Laughs ]

29:48.620 --> 29:49.705
Get over here.

29:49.705 --> 29:53.125
♪ So ♪

29:53.125 --> 29:56.128
♪ She says it's time she goes ♪

29:56.128 --> 29:59.131
Milo, what are
you doing here?

29:59.131 --> 30:01.508
I heard there was
a going‐away party.

30:01.508 --> 30:02.551
How did you ‐‐

30:02.551 --> 30:03.969
Sophie texted me.

30:03.969 --> 30:05.554
♪ ...be friends ♪

30:05.554 --> 30:08.015
♪♪

30:08.015 --> 30:09.182
♪ I think ♪

30:09.182 --> 30:11.059
Do you want to
come in?

30:11.059 --> 30:13.645
No, I just thought I'd iron this
shirt to say I can't make it.

30:13.645 --> 30:15.856
[ Chuckles ]

30:15.856 --> 30:20.610
♪ But didn't think
to ask her why ♪

30:20.610 --> 30:24.406
♪ She blocked her eyes
and drew the curtains ♪

30:24.406 --> 30:26.116
♪ With knots
I've got yet to untie ♪

30:26.116 --> 30:28.493
I'm gonna miss you two.

30:28.493 --> 30:30.495
Aww.

30:30.495 --> 30:34.374
Well, you know, the first night
I met you, we hung out out here.

30:36.084 --> 30:37.586
That was the day
I buried Jon.

30:37.586 --> 30:42.466
♪♪

30:42.466 --> 30:45.177
And the day I met you.

30:45.177 --> 30:48.055
It was also the day
I got my restaurant.

30:50.140 --> 30:52.684
And the day I met you.

30:52.684 --> 30:54.269
[ Laughter ]

30:54.269 --> 30:58.023
♪ What if I was Romeo
in black jeans? ♪

30:58.023 --> 31:02.694
♪ What if I was Heathcliff?
It's no myth ♪

31:02.694 --> 31:05.864
♪ Maybe she's just looking for ♪

31:05.864 --> 31:07.282
Eddie: Root beer?

31:07.282 --> 31:09.117
Taking a move
from my playbook.

31:09.117 --> 31:10.786
Oh, it's for
Danny's boyfriend.

31:10.786 --> 31:13.246
Gary just asked him to name
his top‐three movie villains,

31:13.246 --> 31:15.290
and Milo's never seen
"Die Hard."

31:15.290 --> 31:17.918
It's getting pretty ugly
out there.

31:17.918 --> 31:20.170
[ Laughs ]

31:20.170 --> 31:22.339
Hey, D.

31:22.339 --> 31:24.341
Just so you know,
if you take Charlie to France,

31:24.341 --> 31:26.510
I'm gonna sue you
for everything you have.

31:26.510 --> 31:28.345
Just kidding.

31:28.345 --> 31:29.930
Bon voyage!

31:29.930 --> 31:31.765
[ Laughs ] Wow.

31:31.765 --> 31:33.350
[ Chuckles ]

31:33.350 --> 31:35.102
Hey, who you texting?

31:35.102 --> 31:36.520
Everyone you know
is here.

31:36.520 --> 31:39.439
I'm just checking in with
the nurse at the hospital

31:39.439 --> 31:41.775
to see if there's
any news on my dad.

31:41.775 --> 31:42.776
[ Sighs ]

31:42.776 --> 31:47.030
D, I am so sorry.

31:47.030 --> 31:48.532
He was
everything to me.

31:48.532 --> 31:50.075
Is.

31:50.075 --> 31:51.118
You know,
he's still here.

31:51.118 --> 31:53.495
Mm, no, he's not.

31:53.495 --> 31:55.497
He hasn't been
for awhile.

31:55.497 --> 31:59.167
These last few years
with his memory going,

31:59.167 --> 32:01.128
it's like it was
his last gift ‐‐

32:01.128 --> 32:03.255
help me wean off of him.

32:05.340 --> 32:08.802
Excuse us!
Parade coming through!

32:08.802 --> 32:11.012
Well, half a parade.

32:11.012 --> 32:13.056
Come on, Charlie.

32:13.056 --> 32:15.809
Maybe next time you visit,
we'll all be walking.

32:15.809 --> 32:23.567
♪♪

32:23.567 --> 32:24.901
[ Sighs ]

32:24.901 --> 32:28.238
♪♪

32:28.238 --> 32:29.739
Regina and I
talked about it,

32:29.739 --> 32:32.242
and if you want to go,
we'll pay for the ticket.

32:32.242 --> 32:33.743
Yeah,
we looked it up.

32:33.743 --> 32:37.080
We can use miles for a flight
leaving late tonight.

32:37.080 --> 32:40.500
What about all the plans
we made for the summer?

32:40.500 --> 32:43.461
Oh, we ‐‐ we can still do
all those things.

32:43.461 --> 32:46.798
But if you want to go see
your mom, we support that, too.

32:46.798 --> 32:51.970
♪♪

32:51.970 --> 32:55.307
Uh, if it's okay with you,
I...

32:55.307 --> 32:59.060
I really want to go see
my mom.

32:59.060 --> 33:00.979
Then that's
what you'll do.

33:00.979 --> 33:02.439
Yeah?
Yeah, of course.

33:02.439 --> 33:06.151
♪♪

33:06.151 --> 33:08.028
Martin: Hello?

33:08.028 --> 33:09.779
Oh, hey, guys,
he's here.

33:09.779 --> 33:11.615
He's here.
Delilah: Who's here?

33:11.615 --> 33:13.533
The photographer who took
pictures of my condo.

33:13.533 --> 33:15.327
Yeah, we thought we could do
one last family photo.

33:15.327 --> 33:16.703
Yeah, word is, D, uh,

33:16.703 --> 33:18.705
you opened up a big space
on the wall last night.

33:18.705 --> 33:20.040
[ Laughter ]

33:20.040 --> 33:21.917
See, that
I won't miss.

33:21.917 --> 33:24.336
Alright, line us up.

33:24.336 --> 33:26.504
Alright, great.
Uh, just chin up there a little.

33:26.504 --> 33:27.964
Hey, can you squeeze in there
just a little bit?

33:27.964 --> 33:29.716
Oh, yeah, but you got to get my
good side ‐‐ my good side.

33:29.716 --> 33:31.176
I thought that was
your good side.

33:31.176 --> 33:32.510
Right. Right, right, right,
right, right.

33:32.510 --> 33:33.845
Tyrell: Would you please let
the man do his job?

33:33.845 --> 33:34.679
I got a bag to pack.

33:34.679 --> 33:36.056
[ Laughter ]

33:36.056 --> 33:37.515
Charlie's headband.

33:37.515 --> 33:39.392
Oh, wait, I got it.
One sec.

33:39.392 --> 33:40.894
Oh.

33:40.894 --> 33:44.022
Well, I'll grab some
test shots here.

33:44.022 --> 33:46.274
[ Camera shutter clicking ]
[ Indistinct conversations ]

33:46.274 --> 33:50.403
♪ What if I was Heathcliff?
It's no myth ♪

33:50.403 --> 33:52.614
Oh, thank God you
found my headband.

33:52.614 --> 33:53.990
I'm supposed to play tennis
in the morning.

33:53.990 --> 33:55.367
Thank you.

33:55.367 --> 33:57.369
[ Clears throat ]

33:57.369 --> 33:59.496
How you doing with
everything, huh?

33:59.496 --> 34:02.916
Well, I mean, my family
is moving away,

34:02.916 --> 34:04.960
but my mom said that I can
stay in the house

34:04.960 --> 34:06.962
while we
put it on the market.
Score.

34:06.962 --> 34:09.297
My plan is to use a different
bathroom every day.

34:09.297 --> 34:10.840
I did that
when I stayed here.

34:10.840 --> 34:11.967
It's super fun.

34:14.552 --> 34:16.471
Actually, I was talking about
what happened to Peter.

34:18.014 --> 34:19.391
Maggie told me.

34:23.019 --> 34:25.647
It's crazy, right?

34:25.647 --> 34:27.399
I mean,
when I first heard,

34:27.399 --> 34:29.734
it felt like he got what
he deserved, you know?

34:29.734 --> 34:32.445
Yeah. I do.

34:32.445 --> 34:35.073
But then I realized that
if Peter's in a coma,

34:35.073 --> 34:37.325
then it means he didn't hear
what I said to him

34:37.325 --> 34:39.577
on Maggie's podcast.

34:39.577 --> 34:42.205
And a large reason why
I wanted to do the podcast

34:42.205 --> 34:44.582
is so he'd hear me tell
everybody the truth.

34:47.085 --> 34:48.962
And now I don't know
if he ever will.

34:48.962 --> 34:53.133
♪♪

34:53.133 --> 34:56.636
I just wanted him to know that
I'm stronger than he is.

34:56.636 --> 35:03.059
♪♪

35:08.356 --> 35:10.734
[ Door opens ]

35:10.734 --> 35:12.819
[ Sighs ]

35:14.779 --> 35:15.864
[ Keys thud ]

35:15.864 --> 35:17.824
[ Cellphone ringing ]

35:22.621 --> 35:24.289
[ Cellphone beeps ]

35:24.289 --> 35:25.290
Hello?

35:25.290 --> 35:26.750
Woman:
Is this Maggie Bloom?

35:26.750 --> 35:28.501
Who is this?

35:28.501 --> 35:32.172
It's Jane Goodman,
the station manager from WZLN.

35:32.172 --> 35:35.592
Oh. Um, hi.

35:35.592 --> 35:37.552
How are you?
[ Chuckles ]

35:37.552 --> 35:40.221
I'm sure by now you've seen
the clip of Dr. Stacy

35:40.221 --> 35:41.681
that has gone viral.

35:41.681 --> 35:43.475
I have.

35:43.475 --> 35:47.729
Uh, candidly, I'm responsible
for about 20 of those clicks.

35:47.729 --> 35:49.147
[ Chuckles ]

35:49.147 --> 35:50.732
Well, you know, the only
other clip we have

35:50.732 --> 35:52.817
that has gotten anywhere close
to that kind of attention

35:52.817 --> 35:55.570
was of you quitting
on air.

35:55.570 --> 35:58.948
Well, now you know what
I was dealing with.

35:58.948 --> 36:02.077
Today was not the first time I
had become aware of it, Maggie.

36:02.077 --> 36:03.453
It was just
the last time I could,

36:03.453 --> 36:05.830
in good conscience,
look the other way.

36:05.830 --> 36:07.415
Oh, that's good timing.

36:07.415 --> 36:09.459
Your conscience kicked in
just in time

36:09.459 --> 36:11.336
for your listeners
to hear all about it.

36:11.336 --> 36:14.255
That is what I always liked
about you on Dr. Stacy's show.

36:14.255 --> 36:16.383
You are not afraid
to speak your mind.

36:16.383 --> 36:18.343
Okay, I‐I'm gonna
get right to it.

36:18.343 --> 36:22.180
I just had dinner with
Bob Metcalf from the ZLN board.

36:22.180 --> 36:25.016
We would like to invite
you to be the guest host
for the next two weeks

36:25.016 --> 36:27.727
while we look for Stacy's
permanent replacement.

36:27.727 --> 36:29.688
Really?

36:29.688 --> 36:32.399
Uh, w‐why me?

36:32.399 --> 36:36.152
Well, for starters,
unlike Dr. Stacy,

36:36.152 --> 36:37.821
who's PhD is
in agriculture,

36:37.821 --> 36:40.657
yours is actually in
the field of psychology.

36:40.657 --> 36:42.242
Plus, you're the biggest
name we could get

36:42.242 --> 36:45.662
that understands
this is only a temporary gig.

36:45.662 --> 36:48.915
Honesty, that's ‐‐ that's
an interesting approach.

36:48.915 --> 36:50.834
[ Chuckles ]
I like it.

36:50.834 --> 36:52.836
You're ‐‐ You're
very good at sales.

36:52.836 --> 36:54.337
So is that a yes?

36:55.964 --> 36:59.217
Um, under one condition.

36:59.217 --> 37:01.720
I get to
choose my producer.

37:01.720 --> 37:02.887
I want it to be Claudia.

37:02.887 --> 37:05.181
Dr. Stacy's contract
required the station

37:05.181 --> 37:07.100
to put a personal stylist
on retainer

37:07.100 --> 37:09.394
for clothes worn
on a radio show.

37:09.394 --> 37:11.563
I think we can
afford Claudia.

37:11.563 --> 37:13.356
Sandra from business affairs
is gonna call you

37:13.356 --> 37:14.983
first thing in the morning
and work out the details.

37:14.983 --> 37:16.067
See you soon.

37:16.067 --> 37:17.694
Okay.

37:17.694 --> 37:22.782
♪♪

37:22.782 --> 37:24.784
Gary: Knock‐knock!

37:24.784 --> 37:26.578
Hey, man.

37:26.578 --> 37:29.497
Darce and I are about to
call it a night.

37:29.497 --> 37:30.707
You good?

37:30.707 --> 37:32.459
Yeah, man, just, uh,

37:32.459 --> 37:34.794
looking at photos from tonight
of me, Theo, and Charlie.

37:34.794 --> 37:36.254
Aww.

37:36.254 --> 37:38.173
Yeah, between the blonde one
and the Asian one,

37:38.173 --> 37:40.467
you've got some
pretty weird sperm.

37:40.467 --> 37:41.885
It's like tofu ‐‐

37:41.885 --> 37:43.511
just takes on the flavor
of whatever it's cooked with.

37:43.511 --> 37:44.804
I'm into it.

37:44.804 --> 37:47.015
Yeah. Yeah,
you're doing great.

37:47.015 --> 37:48.892
Another five minutes
of material,

37:48.892 --> 37:50.185
you're gonna have yourself
a tight five.

37:50.185 --> 37:52.645
Ha! Eat it.

37:52.645 --> 37:54.063
[ Door closes ]

37:54.063 --> 38:02.530
♪♪

38:02.530 --> 38:04.199
Woman: I'm the one
who hit you.

38:04.199 --> 38:06.159
I wanted to
say I'm sorry.

38:06.159 --> 38:07.452
How did you
get my number?

38:07.452 --> 38:10.455
[ Clicks key ]

38:10.455 --> 38:12.540
Man: Hey, we need you
on the register.

38:12.540 --> 38:14.959
Okay, I'm coming.
Attention,
Halpert's customers...

38:14.959 --> 38:16.252
[ Inhales sharply ]

38:16.252 --> 38:17.545
Halpert's.

38:17.545 --> 38:26.304
♪♪

38:26.304 --> 38:30.350
This is temporary.
Till he comes back.

38:30.350 --> 38:33.603
And what happens if
he doesn't come back?

38:33.603 --> 38:35.730
Then we did everything
we were supposed to do.

38:35.730 --> 38:37.607
We took care of Martine's son
while she couldn't.

38:37.607 --> 38:44.072
♪♪

38:44.072 --> 38:45.532
[ Light switch clicks ]

38:45.532 --> 38:49.494
♪♪

38:49.494 --> 38:53.540
Rome, come here.
He left this for us.

38:53.540 --> 38:54.666
What is...

38:56.876 --> 38:59.921
Hey, Fosters.
Just wanted to say thanks.

38:59.921 --> 39:03.174
My mom and I are so lucky
that you're in our lives.

39:03.174 --> 39:06.135
Also, Rome...I'm taking
your headphones.

39:06.135 --> 39:08.012
I hope that's okay with you.

39:08.012 --> 39:10.056
I'll bring 'em back
in a few weeks.

39:10.056 --> 39:12.976
A few weeks?
Did you hear that?

39:12.976 --> 39:14.352
Of course
he's coming back.

39:14.352 --> 39:17.105
He...

39:17.105 --> 39:20.400
Yeah. I love you guys.

39:20.400 --> 39:22.318
Oh, my...

39:22.318 --> 39:23.152
Play it again.
Play it again.

39:23.152 --> 39:24.362
Oh, way ahead of you.

39:25.697 --> 39:27.490
Hey, Fosters.
Just wanted to say thanks.

39:27.490 --> 39:29.909
My mom and I are so lucky...

39:29.909 --> 39:33.872
♪♪

39:33.872 --> 39:37.625
Hey, is there something
you're not telling me?

39:37.625 --> 39:41.087
Like what?

39:41.087 --> 39:44.132
The floss is exactly where
I left it two nights ago.

39:44.132 --> 39:45.508
I'm telling
Dr. Morewitz.

39:45.508 --> 39:47.802
[ Chuckles ]

39:47.802 --> 39:50.930
Dr. Morewitz and I
have an understanding.

39:50.930 --> 39:52.056
[ Sighs ]

39:52.056 --> 40:01.816
♪♪

40:01.816 --> 40:02.984
Shut up!
Get off!

40:02.984 --> 40:04.277
Get off!
Get off of me!

40:04.277 --> 40:05.528
Help!

40:05.528 --> 40:08.573
[ Grunting ]

40:08.573 --> 40:11.075
Help me! Somebody!
Please! Somebody!

40:11.075 --> 40:13.786
Shh!

40:13.786 --> 40:15.246
[ Grunts ]

40:15.246 --> 40:16.414
Anybody see you?

40:18.166 --> 40:19.208
No.

40:19.208 --> 40:21.586
[ Grunting ]

40:21.586 --> 40:25.131
Let go of me!

40:25.131 --> 40:26.758
Please!

40:26.758 --> 40:36.684
♪♪

40:36.684 --> 40:38.353
[ Whispering ]
Dr. Morewitz.

40:38.353 --> 40:39.479
She'll be out of
the shower any second.

40:39.479 --> 40:41.147
[ Chuckles ]

40:41.147 --> 40:50.156
♪♪

40:54.744 --> 41:04.337
♪♪

